      "message": "nit: Generally I get uneasy when not using defer to unlock a mutex. Especially in cases where there are multiple returns, I much prefer to call an anonymous function, i.e.:\n\nvar rv *baseline.ComitableBaseLine\nfunc() {\n  b.mutex.RLock()\n  defer b.mutex.RUnlock()\n  cpxTile :\u003d b.currCpxTile\n  // If no commit hash was given use current HEAD.\n  if commitHash \u003d\u003d \"\" {\n    // If we have no tile yet, we cannot get the HEAD of it.\n    if cpxTile \u003d\u003d nil {\n      rv \u003d baseline.EmptyBaseline(nil, nil)\n      return\n    }\n    // Get the last commit that has data.\n    allCommits :\u003d cpxTile.AllCommits()\n    commitHash \u003d allCommits[len(allCommits)-1].Hash\n  }\n  if bLine, ok :\u003d b.baselineCache[commitHash]; ok {\n    rv \u003d bLine.DeepCopyBaseline()\n  }\n}()\nif rv !\u003d nil {\n  return rv, nil\n}",
